  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lambs Support Village Girls&apos; Education</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project buys a lamb &amp; school materials for a girl&apos;s first year of school. Parents raise &amp; sell the lamb, &amp; purchase a new lamb each year thereafter to pay for their daughters&apos; school needs the following 12 years of school.   Through this self-help and sustainable strategy, an initial $80 donation (investment) sends a girl through 13 years of primary - secondary school.  84% of girls enrolled in school through this project have passed national year end exams vs. 64% of students in the region.</narrative>
  </description>
